---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
const tools = await getCollection('tools');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Voice Tools Directory — a curated open-source directory of voice AI tools."
>
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 space-y-10">
    <section>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About Voice Tools Directory</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Voice Tools Directory is an open-source, community-maintained directory of voice AI tools
        curated specifically for <strong>content creators</strong>, <strong>game developers</strong>,
        and <strong>voice AI builders</strong>. Unlike general AI tool aggregators, we focus on
        what actually matters for each user group: licensing clarity, pricing transparency, and
        realistic capability assessments.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Why we built this</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5">→</span>
          <span>Most AI directories list hundreds of tools with no context on licensing — we prioritize "YouTube monetizable?", "game use OK?", "commercial use allowed?"</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5">→</span>
          <span>Real pricing data, not just "contact us" — we track <a href="/changelog" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">pricing changes</a> over time</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5">→</span>
          <span>AI-friendly: structured JSON API and <a href="/llms.txt" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">llms.txt</a> so AI assistants can answer "what's the best TTS for my budget?" accurately</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">The data</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Every tool is manually curated. Data is stored as Markdown files in a public GitHub
        repository. We never fill in fields we can't verify — if we don't know the latency,
        it's not on the page.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold">{tools.length}</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Tools indexed</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold">10</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Categories</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold">0</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Paid placements</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Contributing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The directory is open source. Adding a tool takes ~30 seconds: create one Markdown file,
        fill in the frontmatter, open a PR. See the <a href="/submit" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Submit a Tool</a> page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">License</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">
        Code: <strong>MIT</strong>. Tool data: <strong>CC BY 4.0</strong>.
        You're free to use the data in your own projects with attribution.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
